{"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"],"fields":{"title":{"boost":1000.0},"text":{"boost":1.0},"tags":{"boost":1000000.0}}},"docs":[{"location":"","title":"OrbitLab","text":"<p>OrbitLab is a lightweight Python package for unit-safe orbital mechanics simulations.</p>"},{"location":"#features","title":"Features","text":"<ul> <li>Orbital velocity calculations</li> <li>Escape velocity calculations</li> <li>Orbit trajectory simulation</li> <li>Numba-accelerated numerical integration</li> <li>Pint-powered unit safety</li> </ul>"},{"location":"#installation","title":"Installation","text":"<p><code>bash</code> pip install orbitlab</p>"},{"location":"api/","title":"API","text":""},{"location":"api/#gravitational-force","title":"Gravitational Force","text":"<p>Computes gravitational force between two masses.</p>"},{"location":"api/#orbital-velocity","title":"Orbital Velocity","text":"<p>Computes circular orbital velocity.</p>"},{"location":"api/#simulate-orbit","title":"Simulate Orbit","text":"<p>Runs a 2D orbital simulation.</p>"},{"location":"physics/","title":"Physics Background","text":"<p>OrbitLab uses Newtonian gravity.</p>"},{"location":"physics/#gravitational-force","title":"Gravitational Force","text":"<p>F = G m\u2081 m\u2082 / r\u00b2</p>"},{"location":"physics/#orbital-velocity","title":"Orbital Velocity","text":"<p>v = sqrt(GM/r)</p>"},{"location":"physics/#numerical-integration","title":"Numerical Integration","text":"<p>The simulation updates:</p> <ul> <li>position</li> <li>velocity</li> <li>acceleration</li> </ul> <p>using Euler integration.</p>"}]}